WEBVTT

00:03:29.533 --> 00:03:31.058
"Who do you report to?"

00:03:31.970 --> 00:03:33.247
"It depends."

00:03:33.940 --> 00:03:36.125
"Who decides on your priorities?"

00:03:36.919 --> 00:03:38.168
"It depends."

00:03:38.785 --> 00:03:40.573
You can imagine our surprise.

00:03:40.597 --> 00:03:43.957
We were asking for what we thought
were some of the basic principles

00:03:43.981 --> 00:03:45.154
of organizations,

00:03:45.178 --> 00:03:47.968
and their answer was, "It depends."

00:03:49.404 --> 00:03:51.013
Now, over the course of that day,

00:03:51.037 --> 00:03:53.548
we gained a better
understanding of their model.

00:03:53.572 --> 00:03:57.490
They believed in the power
of small, autonomous teams.

00:03:57.514 --> 00:03:59.439
Their teams were like mini-start-ups.

00:03:59.463 --> 00:04:03.069
They had product people
and IT engineers in the same team